	A Good Value in Downtown Las Vegas	I just returned from a 6-night stay at the Four Queens. The room was a little dated, but it was clean and comfortable. There's an ironing board and iron in the room, and I really appreciated having a coffee maker in the room. There was also a safe that was more than big enough to fit my laptop, which was good.Some people I talked to said that the water pressure in their shower was way too high, making it uncomfortable, but that wasn't a problem for me. The bathroom was very small, though.The hotel is in a great location, with the Fremont Street Experience right outside the door, so I was able to go down and see whichever shows I wanted to see throughout the week without making a special trip. Also, the Deuce bus to the Strip and the outlet stores is nearby, so that's really convenient. I stayed on the Strip once before, and you have to take a bus to get up and down it anyway, so staying downtown seemed better to me. I got to see whatever I wanted to on the Strip, but I saw more of Fremont Street than I would have otherwise.Plus, the Four Queens Casino was one of the few places I found that had 9/6 jacks or better video poker. I managed to get a royal flush, so the trip more than payed for itself!	
