Oct 10 2009 	It was a comfortable fun experience from check-in to check out.	The rooms are not the fanciest I've stayed in, but our room was clean and comfortable, with windows that actually opened to allow fresh air into the room (a rarity these days, and much appreciated!), and a sizeable flat-screen television with a good selection of channels. The hotel has reasonably priced internet service (about half the price of the hotel we stayed in on &quot;the Strip.&quot; From the moment we checked in until the moment we checked out, the hotel staff members were invariably friendly and accommodating. The hotel's restaurant serves delicious chicken fried steak, among many other delicious offerings. It is one of the better restaurants in the casinos in downtown Las Vegas. (I also recommend the buffet at the Main Street Station hotel / casino). The Fremont Street light show was fun, and the &quot;Summer of '69 Woodstock TributePalooza&quot; free musical entertainment was also a good show. The Four Queens Casino has affordable ($3 and $5) tables for those of us who don't like to &quot;bet the house,&quot; and a huge variety of fun slots. Additionally, unlike some of the &quot;high end&quot; casinos on the strip, the coctail waitresses actually serve the penny slot machines and bring your drinks back fairly quickly. And, we won money! What could be better, really? We'll definitely return!	
