Aug 3 2009 	What a deal!	I stayed at the Four Queens after doing research on Tripadvisor. My husand and I took a long weekend trip to celebrate our 10th anniversary, wished it was longer. I have absolutely no complaints about the Four Queens. All the staff we encountered were very friendly. We had free breakfast every morning at Magnolia's, basic but good (liked the sourdough toast). I received a buy one get one free dinner, since it was my birthday through the player's club. We both ordered the NY strip dinners at Magnolia's and thought they were pretty good. I had a $20 voucher for slot playing, so I did a little gambling (not a big gambler), won a few bucks. Within a few minutes of sitting at a slot machine a cocktail waitress was there offering drinks each time. The room is small but very comfortable, great air conditioning and shower, and clean. I went back to my room while it was being cleaned to change into tennis shoes after walking a bit (I think we walked ten miles that morning just checking the sites on the strip) and the cleaning lady was very nice, but requested I use my key to get into my room, very good to know your belongings are secure. I gave her a two dollar tip and asked for more coffee, and she was extremely appreciative. We came back later that night and had a surplus of coffee, shampoo, soap, and towels. I have stayed at Bally's, Harrah's, and MGM in the past. I paid significantly more for the room, they are all fine, but I enjoyed my time at the Four Queens more. More bang for significantly less buck.	
