Jul 29 2009 	Good Value - I Would Stay There Again	We arrived around 1pm on Saturday. There was no line at Registration. We were able to check-in, though the official check-in time is 4pm. The staff was friendly and helpful, explaining the free parking pass system for guests.The room was nice for the price. It was a renovated room. We had a king sized bed, flat screen TV, iron and ironing board, hair dryer, clock radio, AC, and room safe large enough for a laptop. There were two nightstands, a combo dresser/TV stand, small desk for the coffee maker, a larger desk, and an ottoman. Also, lots of hangers in the closet instead of the usual 4-6. The bathroom was small, but the water pressure was good.The only complaint we had was that our non-smoking room came with ash trays and had a really strong smoke smell. We have experienced this before in other downtown hotels, so we weren't really surprised. The downtown hotels are so old that the smoke from all the previous years have permeated everything OR the non-smoking room is really just any room and the guests can choose to smoke or not OR they put us on the first/best available room. Bringing an Airwick or Plug-In Air Freshener would easily remedy this.Subway and Roman Noble (or Noble Roman) Pizza is open until 3am. DO NOT EAT at the hotel cafe Magnolia's. The French Dip was awful, the meat was super dry. The grilled chicken breast was bland as well. The fries were soggy. Since the hotel is on Fremont St., I would recommend Tony Roma's across the way or one of the many restaurants/bars on the street or in the other casinos.Overall, the service was good and friendly. The location is great. You can walk the 3-4 blocks of Fremont (West) and experience numerous casinos, restaurants and bars. The Fremont Experience light and music show was hit and miss. I loved KISS, but was unimpressed by the 60s themed show. The show runs for 20 min at the top of every hour from 8pm-12am. It's loud enough that you can hear it in the room, but it didn't bother us.The room was a good value for the price, and we would stay there again.	
