Jul 20 2009 	Looking for value and comfort? Look no further	If you are after a place to stay that is clean comfortable and has friendly staff then the 4 Queens is the place for you. Ok its downtown in &quot;Old Style Vegas&quot; but there is still a lot to do in the area. And if you want to commute to the strip the bus ($3) is only a block away or a cab costs just $10 (make sure the cabbie goes straight down Vegas Blvd not out on the highway or its gonna come to $18 - $20). The value is outstanding having stayed there for 17 nights for a total of $540 in June/July, room service came every single day, the rooms are very clean and the air conditioning is excellent. Put it this way, who spends that much time in their room whilst in Vegas anyway? The service is fantastic, just pick up the phone and they are there with whatever you need in just a few minutes. The store downstairs is great for convenience and there is a walgreens (supermarket) just one block away. One of the highlights downtown is the Fremont Street Experience. Live music every night, festivals on the weekend and the unbelievable light show makes it truly one of a kind. The restaurants in the area are very good and great value. Magnolias and the Chicago Brewing Co at the 4 Queens are both great. Binions has the best cheeseburgers in the area and hennesys does really good homestyle meals at great prices. The best buffet by far is at the Golden Nugget with a great variety including asian and seafood. As for the casino's themselves they cant match the huge buildings on the strip but they are fun and functional and the limits are low with games such as 50c roulette, $2 blackjack and $3 craps. I stayed in the north tower which seems to be a bit newer than the other one. Checking in is easy and quick and there is no problem checking in early or out late provided the rooms aren't required immediately. Overall i would say if you need a place to stay that is comfortable and great value for money you cannot go past the 4 Queens. Most people go to Vegas to gamble or to do tours of the landmarks, so save your money for these things.	
