Jun 6 2009 	Great Value for the Money	While the structure is Old Vegas, the rooms have been updated and upgraded and are very comfortable, and very clean. The Fremont Street location allows you to get out and walk to other casinos/hotels, restaurants, gift shops, a multi-screen theatre, etc. If you don't want to have to drive everywhere, this is a plus. And the Strip is only eight minutes away by car. Currently, the Four Queens adds on a small parking fee ($3 per day), if you use their parking garage. While other casinos/hotels on Fremont offer free parking, I didn't mind this small additional fee, since the room was so comfortable. We also had very hot water in the bathroom, something that seems to be inconsistent among some of the older hotels there on Fremont St. That alone was worth the $3.We liked it well enough that we're booking another four nights there, versus other hotels with slightly lower daily rates. I would recommend the Four Queens to anyone, without hesitation or reservation.	
