May 21 2009 	Nice Stay at the Four Queens	Just got home from a 4 night stay at the Four Queens Hotel And Casino. This was the first time I have stayed downtown in Las Vegas. The hotel is older and it shows in a lot of ways, yet it was clean, housekeeping was very good, I always had hot water for showers, the bed was comfortable, and there was a coffeemaker in the room. My room was on the tenth floor on the Fremont street side of the building so it was very noisy in the evenings until the last Fremont Street Experience show at midnight, but, it still wasn't that bad. The room wasn't huge, but was very adequate for me as a solo traveler. Downtown was a lot different than the strip (for one thing, as others have noted, there are none of the &quot;porn-slappers&quot; downtown). It was very nice to be able to walk short distances between places, instead of girding for the hike to get anywhere downtown. As a person alone, with no set itinerary, I had no problem getting from downtown to the strip using the Sam's Town shuttle. It has two stops downtown, then goes directly to Sam's Town. From Sam's Town it goes to Harrah's and then Riviera so you have the option of mid strip or north strip. The shuttle was never more than half full and it was all just tourists like myself. It is very prompt and the drivers were always friendly. I would recommend downtown Las Vegas and the Four Queens to anyone looking for a less hectic (and less expensive) alternative to the Strip.	
