Apr 20 2009 	Great value 	My husband &amp; I stayed at the Four Queens from April 10th to April 12th, 2009. Based on Trip Advisor reviews, the location &amp; the price through Expedia, we deceided to give the 4 Queens a chance. We were NOT dissappointed. We got a regular room next to the Fremont Street Experience. Since we were out until after midnight every night, having room next to FSE did not bother us at all.Our experience at the Check-in counter was fast &amp; friendly. We did find out that there is a $3.00 per night charge for the parking garage, but that was fine with us. Not having to find a place to park each night was worth the $3.00 charge. We were given a parking pass to show the garage attendant &amp; remember to keep your little white ticket. You need to give it to the attendant each time you leave the parking garage. Our room was cozy, but very clean. Hotels we have stayed at on the strip were not as clean as our room at Four Queens was. We were pleasantly surpirsed by this. Our bed was comfortable but our door always seemed to slam shut, even when were trying to close it quietly. Once we got into our room, we could not hear people through paper thin walls. We just heard the occassional door slam shut. It was no big deal to us.Something people may want to know about is that in the tower we stayed in, there is not an ice machince on each floor. There was one on ours, but we just found that a little unusual. Our room had a coffee maker, hair dryer &amp; a televison with a decent selection of channels. Who spends much time inside a hotel room in Las Vegas anyway!We really enjoyed our stay at the Four Queens &amp; will stay here again. We did not have a good dining expereince at Magnolia's. Our food was bland &amp; the service was &quot;okay&quot; at best. The slots were fun &amp; payed out pretty well. Our favorite part was the Roulette table. We stopped by there 3 times &amp; each time the person running the table was both helpful &amp; knowledgeable. We enjoyed having everything we could want within walking distance. Walgreens is less than a 5 minute walk away. Four Queens does not have a swimming pool, but we were told at check-in that Binion's lets the guests of Four Queens use their swimming pool. I would not bring my children to this hotel, but it was fine for just the two of us.	
