Apr 11 2009 	Four Queens Treated Me Like Royalty	My seventh trip to Vegas was complete with a stay at the Four Queens. I've stayed at the Rio, MGM and the like, and knowing that most hotel rooms differ mostly monetarily as opposed to aesthetically, I chose this hotel simply looking for clean accomodations, and a break from the overcrowded strip. And, I found exactly what I was looking for. After a shuttle drop-off, I arrived for a late check-in (9 pm) and the gentleman at the counter couldn't have been more considerate. When I received my room keys for a suite (an upgrade), I found a clean room with a flat screen tv, large bathroom, and despite it's closeness to the Fremont Experience, I experienced a nice, serene quiet in the midst of the show's performances. The housekeeping staff was very attentive and hospitable, leaving plenty of towels, and even a new bath rug in the room each night.Now, smoking might be an issue for some. If so, you might seek other arrangements. I'm a non-smoker, and the smoke was apparent when I approached the elevators, but fortunately, the smells were limited to the casino area. I didn't get a chance to eat at Hugo's or Magnolia's but heard good things about them both. In the end, Downtown Vegas was all that I needed and more than I expected. I cleaned up on the cash there too (Fitzgerald and Fremont slots, no less), so I am certain to return to FQ. It's a certainty.	
