Mar 20 2009 	Great place at bargain rates!	The 4 Queens Hotel and Casino is located on Fremont Street, next to the Golden Nugget. It's midway along the Freemont Street Experience area. I stayed there March 8 - 13, 2009.The hotel was recently renovated, so that now there are icemakers and vending machines on almost every floor. The rooms are moderately sized but not cramped, with adequate counter space in the bathrooms - which have 4' bathtubs with shower over; and there is plenty of closet space. They are clean and tastefully decorated. I had a plumbing problem in that the shower/tub faucet leaked loudly and with arthritic hands it was impossible to open the faucet valve when it had been forced closed to stop the leak. Hotel maintenance removed the hardware and replaced it within 24 hours of my report. Excellent housekeeping services as well. Where other hotels I've stayed at in Vegas have a card you're requested to leave on the bed if you want the linens changed before you leave (otherwise they are not changed), there were no such cards here and my beds were changed after 3 nights - even though I was only staying 5 nights.Lower floors will include rooms that look out onto the &quot;hardware&quot; of the Fremont Experience jumbotron, but the upper floors offer unobstructed views. If you get a room on the Fremont Street side of the hotel, expect to hear the sound and light show until sometime after midnight nightly. The rooms come with a flat-screen TV, coffeemaker, iron and ironing board. The in-room safe is larger than most; it comprises the area that would otherwise be the bottom drawer of the bedside table - which is bolted to the floor - and allows the room occupant to set his/her own combination.  There are several restaurants located on the casino level, including Hugo's Cellar and Magnolia Cafe. Players club members are offered daily menu specials at Magnolia's. The slot machines include some of the latest released games and are placed such that the casino does not have a &quot;cramped&quot; atmosphere.	
