Dec 17 2008 	Great Downtown Location	My wife and I love downtown Vegas and usually book the majority of our nights there, not on the Strip. When we decided on a weekend trip and couldn't convince the relatives to look after the kids, the Four Queens looked like it would probably suit our needs, especially given the favourable reviews I'd seen. Though not necessarily 'kid friendly', the price is right and the location is perfect.We arrived around 2 on a Friday afternoon, and though the room had not yet been cleaned we were able to get keys and store our luggage there. Check-in was very quick and staff were friendly.We booked a package and chose the 'low end' price, so the room we ended up with was not newly renovated. Though it did have the flat screen TV, the rest was pretty old and we actually had a handicapped bathroom. No big deal but it did make for an awfully high toilet for the kids. Nice to have a coffee maker, ironing board and a large safe, otherwise pretty standard. The room was clean, just tired looking.The big draw here is the location. Really, virtually all the downtown properties are central, but this one is dead center on Fremont Street. Not only that, the access is a breeze since you can go through the doors near the valet and bypass the entire casino. With no waits for the elevator we were able to leave our room and be on Fremont street in about 3 minutes!We didn't eat at any of the restaurants in the hotel/casino, but there is a decent selection. Of course, staying downtown means a quick walk is all it takes to get pretty much any food you want.I have to admit, we love the Gold Spike, and now it is being renovated into a 'boutique' property so we'll see how that pans out. Our philosophy is to sleep cheap and spend the savings on food or entertainment. So...I'd have to say that The Four Queens fit the bill very nicely for us on this trip.	
Dec 13 2008 	great price and very nice room	booked the hotel via hrs.com for a realy great price. the room was excelent and was better then expected. Any time again	
Dec 11 2008 	First Time Staying Downtown	Had been to Vegas many times before and had visited downtown just never stayed there. The 4 Queens was the cheapest option for the days in December I was going, so away I went. I don't spend too much time in my room in Vegas but was impressed with the 4 Queens room. I had a room in the south tower on the 15th floor. Very quiet, very clean, comfy bed (spent about 9hrs total sleeping in 2 nites) , excellent Flat Screen (watched about 10 minutes of the news in 2 nites there) had a safe, only drawback was the size of bathroom but remember this was the cheapest place I could find to stay. A tip is if you are really picky and like to complain stay at really expensive places on the strip. The casino was small but had lots of low limit table games with good pay tables (common downtown I played roulette at Binions and they have $2 min). I signed up for the players card at the 4Q and got a free deck of cards in a collectable tin then had a $8 Prime Rib dinner at Magnolias that was excellent. If you take off the value of the free gift I got, you could say dinner cost me $5! The parking garage costs guest $3 day but remember it's also $15-$20 a nite cheaper here. The garage and hotel are small which I like, makes things less confusing. Clientele was definetly older but I mainly hung out at the Poker rooms in Binions (excellent) and the Golden Nugget. Downtown has lots of cheap food options, beers are $2 all over and t-shirts and such are far cheaper downtown. I still enjoy the strip better but for a couple of nites and if you rent a car downtown can really save you some money.	
