Nov 20 2008 	Best Value in Las Vegas!	Once again the Four Queens exceeded my expectations. Having stayed here 4 times in the last year and a half I can not say enough good things. If you are looking for a fancy lobby and fast elevators this is not the hotel for you. However, if you are on a budget and looking for a great deal this is the place for you. I payed $59 for a Saturday night and $29 for Sun/Mon. Try finding that on the strip. Hotel is clean, safe, and staff is excellent. Was able to get checked in at 9:00 AM on Saturday moning. The hotel is located in the heart of the Fremont Street Experience (can be noisy) so if you value some peace and quiet make sure you request a room facing AWAY from the Fremont Street experience. Also for those of you wanting to go to the strip the bus stop is a stone's throw away. The bus is called the deuce and you get get a 24 hour unlimited ride pass for $5. The Fremont Street Experience really takes off aat night so I usually hit the strip in the day and head back to the Four Queens at night. Chicago Brewing Company (one of their restaurants) has great pizza and beer. Their other restaurant (magnolias) leaves a little bit to be desired. For those of you who insist on staying on the strip you may want to try staying downtown sometime. I think you will be surprised at how affordable and fun it could be. Where on the strip can you walk into a casino bar and buy an ice cold Corona or Heineken for $2.	
