Nov 5 2008 	Our new 'Home Base' in Vegas	Over the past 12 years my wife and I have visited Vegas many times. We have lodged at many different properties both on the strip and downtown. We believe we have found an appropriate 'home base' for our subsequent vists.Check in was a breeze. From the curb to the room in less than 10 minutes. When making reservations I requested a room away from Fremont Street and it was granted. We had room 1015 North tower. The room and bathroom were not large but it was clean and the bed was comfortable. The AC worked well and was fairly quiet but the plumbing noise from the shower was kind of annoying. Housekeeping did a great job and always asked if we needed anything. Coffee makers in the room is a plus. Flatscreen TV also a plus. Checking out was also pain free and quick. I guess I gambled enough on the tables to earn me some comps on the room. Hint: Have the floor folks rate your play at the tables and always use your players card at the slots. Check with the Casino Host or Slot Host before you check out to see if you qualify for any comps. Most of the staff at the Four Queens were helpful and friendly. Other than a couple of grouchy wait staff at Magnolias everyone seemed cheerful. The blackjack and craps dealers were fun, especially on Halloween. Picture a clown supervising a sexy policewoman who is dealing blackjack to three divas. Fun times. Aside from a craps session at O'Shea's, we gambled exclusively at the Four Queens. Whenever we venture out to the strip to catch a show or to see Big Elvis (at least once a trip!) it's only a short walk to The Deuce - the bus stop is at the corner of LV Blvd and Fremont, look for the big glass of beer! For $5 you can get a 24 hour pass that will get you from one end of the strip to the other and back downtown.Good value, good service, good hotel, good gaming, good location downtown. We will definitely be returning the the Four Queens.	
