Aug 12 2008 	Viva 4 Queens!	Going to Vegas for our wedding, we decided to try the Four Queens, based largely on the reviews here. My new bride and I were definitely not disappointed! Our room in the South tower (12th Floor) was clean and comfortable, and room service very efficient. The hotel was ideally located for our needs. The &quot;Deuce&quot; (the bus that runs from downtown to the south end of the Strip) was just two blocks away and plenty of food choices and cheezy souvenir shops awaited right outside the doors. The food at Magnolia's at the 4 Queens was delicious, and if you join the Players' Club (it's free) you can get some nice discounts there, too. And of course you're right in the middle of the Fremont St. Experience. So unless you're trying to earn bragging rights by staying at the very overrated and overpriced big-name properties on the Strip, I'd highly recommend the Four Queens.	
