Jul 13 2008 	Perfect Stay at Four Queens!	As we've stayed on the strip before, we wanted to experience downtown. After doing ALOT of research - we decided on the Four Queens Hotel and we're so pleased with our decision. We got an amazing deal on Expedia ($28/night and then a $50 gas card). We stayed here for 3 nights.While it isn't your glitzy 5 star hotel - it has everything you need and was very comfortable. Our entire trip was extremely smooth - everything from our shuttle from the airport to our check-out at noon. We arrived at the hotel at 10:30 pm and there was no line up (unlike the strip hotels). Our room was exactly what we requested (king/non-smoking). The view wasn't the greatest but that's no big deal - I didn't request a room with a view. The air conditioning was fantastic - no problems. The bathroom is small but manageable and very clean. The housekeeping was great - everyday our room was cleaned. We requested extra pillows - no problem - received soon after requested. The bed was real comforable and the room size was great. The food at Magnolia's was great. Nice home cooked feeling there with very reasonable prices. Make sure to ask for the Funbook when you are checking in. The book has coupons for the hotel's services (meals, coffees, slot $, etc.). We took full advantage of the funbook and probably saved $50.00. The casino is also a great size. It has something for everyone. I really have no complaints about the Four Queens.The Fremont Street Experience was amazing. We never felt scared on the street and there were plenty of security around in case anything were to happen (we didn't see anything bad happen though). Even in 112 degree heat - it was comfortable because the entire street has the canopy that blocks the sun. We were thankful for this!!!Everything is right outside your door - McDonalds, Dunkin Donuts, Starbucks, Walgreens... We took the city bus to the Outlet Mall ($1.25/per person). Great place for shopping. We then cabbed it back to the Four Queens ($12.00 cab fare including tip).After staying downtown, I don't think we will be going back to the strip. We absolutely loved downtown and can't wait to go back. It is a different atmosphere where everyone is friendly and helpful. All ages here - from small babies to the elderly. We will definitely stay at the Four Queens again and would also like to try out the Fremont Hotel.If you are looking for a little more 'glitz' - you would probably like the Golden Nugget... but we did notice that the lobby always had a long line up of people checking in/out - and the pool was also very busy.Tip: Before you go - make sure to register online for the Four Queens players club - print it out and present it for a gift. We got a free duffle bag just for registering online!	
