Apr 11 2008 	Great stay!	Went to the front desk on a Sunday morning around 11am expecting to be turned away until 4pm. The room we booked (standard) was not ready, but after inquiring, was upgraded to a suite in the South tower. Very large room with two couches, table, desk, comfortable bed and adequately sized bathroom. Large flat screen TV, but we never turned it on. Hotel staff provided excellent service (be sure to tip the front desk clerk in appreciation for the work they do on your behalf). If you play table games, be sure to stay on the pit crew about rating your play if you expect to be comped properly. We checked with the casino host after two days of play, and found that we had been significantly under-rated for our level of play. The host spoke with the pit management, and we were properly rated for the remainder of our trip. Overall, a great stay, and will be going back again!	
