Apr 1 2008 	Comfortable stay	My parents, husband and myself all stayed here on our Vegas trip. We booked our stay as part of a package deal combining flight, car and hotel. The first night we were split up on separate floors, my husband and I on the fourth floor, my parents on the fourteenth. The front desk clerk told us that we could move the next day if we wished. We were moved to the fourteenth floor the next day. Despite that floor being a smoking floor (and being a non-smoker), I never noticed any smoky smell.Our bed was so comfortable, and the new plasma screen tv's are really a nice amenity. While the bathroom and room were a bit small it certainly didn't matter as we were hardly in our room. I did notice the doors on that floor for some reason would shut loudly no matter how gingerly you closed them. We didn't have that problem on the fourth floor. Other than that, it was quiet.We dined at Magnolia's Veranda, one of the casino's restaurant's. I had the muffaletta, while everyone else took advantage of the prime rib special. I highly recommend the muffaletta. It was a huge sandwich and was made very well. My husband tried to large beer sampler. It was 9 different beers in mini mugs on a lazy susan. You could try a little of everything. I was pleasantly surprised at the price of the sampler at less than 8 dollars.The hotel's casino opens right onto Fremont Street which is really nice. It was so easy to just walk right out and be in the middle of the action.If I come back to Vegas, I will consider staying at the Four Queens again.	
