t so you better get me it. I was FINALLY able to get my suite, though non-smoking when I booked a smoking room. I said to hell with it and smoked in the room throughout my stay anyways.When I'd order room service I always felt like I was bugging people. When they brought the food up they were always in a rush and barely smiling...so much for that %17 included gratuity fee.I had a late flight that night so after I checked out I gave my bags to the Bell Desk to hold on to until I left. By god, you'd swear I was asking the world of him. I still gave him $5 tip for the EFFORT he put into it....and just because I'm not cheap. I WILL say that the dealers at the table and floor management people were extremely nice and funny and made my gambling time more enjoyable.Casino: Nice casino but they're all very similar.Comps: Unless they mail me special offers or free nights stay, the comps are pretty bad. You have to spend tons of money to get anything. If you're an average to low gambler, it's useless. I still suggest you get a players card made because you never know.Would I stay again at Four Queens? I guess it would depend on the Golden Nugget's rates. If the GN is more expensive then yeah I would...but for 20 bucks more a night I'd probably choose the GN over Four Queens.	
