Feb 18 2008 	Loved it! Will go back	We booked a Vegas package through Cheaptrips and hit the jackpot! We got a smooth nonstop from Seattle to Vegas, and had a wonderful time at the Four Queens. We were on the 5th floor, North Tower, overlooking the Fremont Experience sign. Odd numbered rooms face the experience, even numbers are farther away from the experience nightly activity. Even being so close, we could barely hear the experience and crowds at night. The room was nicely furnished and clean. Nothing extravagant, but we didn't need that. The bathroom wasn't palatial, but didn't need that either. The staff was very friendly and helpful. We ate breakfast at Magnolia's every morning (open 24/7), and the food was delicious, and hot! We had a special dinner at Hugo's and the food and service was exceptional. It was costly, but worth every penny. Wonderful salad prepared especially for each person at your table. Gambling: we just hit the slots, which were a bit more loose Fri-Sun. Nice variety of slots. The cashiers were fun if you talk with them. We've been going to Vegas and staying on the strip for years. We like staying downtown. It's a shorter distance to the various casinos, smaller crowds, friendlier casino staff, looser slots. If you're the younger generation, love the glitz and noise of the strip, downtown isn't for you! We just took a taxi ride to the strip to see our booked shows.	
