Feb 7 2008 	Super Hotel during Super Bowl Weekend!!!	Six of us just returned from our fifth Super Bowl Weekend in Las Vegas. This was our first time staying at the Four Queens and we had an absolutely fantastic time. We stayed five nights (arrived Thursday, departed Tuesday) on the 15th floor of the South Tower where our recently remodeled rooms had new carpet, new furniture, new drapes, new bedding, and a new flat screen TV. Although our bathrooms had not been remodeled and were older, they were still maintained and cleaned. The entire staff, including but not limited to, Check-in, Dealers, Pit Bosses, Cashiers, Waitresses, Bartenders, Security, were friendly, courteous, helpful, and accommodating. We did the majority of our gambling at the Four Queens where the drink service while doing so was expeditious. The food/beverage at Hugos Cellar, Magnolias Veranda, Chicago Brewing Company, and Queens Coffee/Deli was excellent. We have stayed at other Freemont Street hotels and the Four Queens most definitely gives you the best value for your hard earned dollars. Personally, my trip was topped off on the morning of our departure when I decided to give it one more gamble. I played one of the Elvis Slot machines and was rewarded with $413.50 of which I promptly took a portion and made some future bets at the Sports Book. Viva Las Vegas and Viva the Four Queens!!!!!	
