Nov 24 2007 	Loved The Four Queens Nov 11th thru Nov 14th	When I booked my trip for November I decided to try downtown for once. I read all the reviews on the downtown hotels and the most consistent recommendations kept coming from the reviews on the Four Queens Hotel. After staying there, I must agree with the reviews. The Four Queens is a great hotel. I arrived before 12:00 pm and was able to check in as my room was available. The desk clerk was fast and very friendly.  (I usually stay at the Strat and the lines to check in are horrendous). They give you a fun book that has some really good two for one coupons. My room elevators was right off of the lobby area which I found to be very convenient being that you didn't have to walk the entire length of the Casino to get to your room. I give the Four Queens high points for that alone. I was given a room on the 15th floor room 1525. Upon arriving in my room the first thing I noticed was the spaciousness of the room.Two queen beds, flat screen tv and desk.When I entered thebathroom I noticed a handicap chair and bars. They had given me a handicap room. The bathroom was very spacious also.I had asked for a room not facing the Fremont St Exp. but when I looked down I could see the side of the canopy. Although I could hear the music when it started on the hour it was very muted so did not really bother me. My views was mostly of the Golden Nugget and not the mountains in which I am particularly fond of.I found the dining choices at the Four Queens to be a little bit lacking as they have no buffet. Magnolia's is an excellent choice but can get a little crowded around the dinner hour. You have to pick your times to eat there. usually late morning and evening works best. This is a non problem as the Fremont's buffet is directly across the street and on Sundays they have an all day champagne brunch/buffet. There are so many food choices within walking distance of the Four Queens that I never ate at the same place twice. I loved the proximity of the other establishments. I also loved the whole atmosphere of downtown and the entertainment. The Four Queens casino has a good selection of slot machines and they seemed to give you a nice chance of winning. The drink service was quite good also. I overall felt very comfortable gambling in their casino it never felt overcrowded and the people were friendly. I would highly recommend anyone staying downtown and looking for a good budget friendly hotel stay at the Four Queens. I forgot to mention the maid service was also quite good. My room was made up early and plenty of towels were available.	
