Nov 10 2007 	Best place to stay Downtown!	Hubby and I just returned home to Michigan from our best Vegas trip ever! Stayed at the 4 Queens, Downtown. After countless trips making the rounds (Boyd properties, Fitz, Plaza, Vegas Club, Binion's, even splurging for the Golden Nugget) I feel this is the best deal downtown.We checked in on Monday for a four night stay. Check-in staff were friendly and helpful. My husband asked if a suite upgrade would be possible. Yes, we got one for double the room rate we were being charged. It looked exactly like the mini suite in the pic on the website. The armoire has plenty of room on each side of the tv to hide your dirty clothes. :-P It's hard to see in the picture, but there's a fridge with an ice bucket and wine glasses next to the desk and chair. We were on the second floor, but back from the road. I could barely hear the Fremont Street Experience the rare times I was in the room during the evening.We lucked into seeing the Firemen's Combat Challenge World Competition. They were competing right outside the casino.The casino has a half-price ticket outlet. We recommend seeing Larry G. Jones. We saw him back when he did 1001 voices and he was terrific! Thoroughly entertaining. I think he's up to 1003 voices now. We wanted to see him this trip, but he only works weekends now. Good to see him moving up.The 4 Queen's casino personnel are very friendly. My husband played the single deck blackjack until they very politely told him to stop. I played the black jack switch and a new game called California Draw. I don't imagine it will last if everyone is as lucky as I was when Dezdemona taught me the game. She showed me how much trips, two-pair, and even a straight flush paid. I can't wait to go back and try my luck again. The Casino Cage is being remodeled. They were squeezed into a small spot by the restrooms. I never saw less then three cashiers working and never waited in line. Noel was very friendly when he gave me my big winnings from the CA Draw game. We ate at Magnolia's several times. The staff were very smiley and friendly. Wanted to try Hugo's, but too pricey for me. Hubby wanted the $40 rack of lamb. Maybe next time. Even leaving out the fact that I experienced my luckiest night gambling here, I think the Four Queens is the best deal downtown. The suite was clean and roomy. The staff are friendly and helpful. And, the location can't be beat. We were in the tower farther from Fremont St, but were still only steps away from the casino and the action outside on the street.	
