Oct 16 2007 	Not bad but avoid the North Tower	The hotel overall is nice. The casino has a wide-range of table and machine games. The restaurants are good and the service is friendly. The biggest gripe that I have is the hotel didn't warn me when I checked in that my room overlooked the Fremont Experience. I stayed out until late so I missed the loud shows from the Experience. But what I didn't anticipate was the music that's played through the speakers doesn't stop. So all through the night I heard the booming bass and the rest of the music. The hotel should advise guests that their room faces the Fremont Experience and that if they wanted to get some peace and quiet then they should ask for a different room. Since I don't think that this will happen, avoid the rooms in the hotel's North Tower, especially the rooms that face the Experience.	
