Sep 18 2007 	Would Stay Again	We were in Vegas for a eight day trip staying at three different properties while in town over the Labor Day holiday. This was our first time staying at this hotel, so we were anxious to see what it would be like since we had heard it was recently refurbished. We booked our room over the phone with a casino rate based on our play from our previous visit in May. We did not receive a mail offer and had to call to ask for the casino rate. Check in was very easy with no line at all. The front desk clerk was very cordial and made the experience very pleasant. Our room was in the south tower, room 1033 for four nights. We had a king, n/s room. The accommodations were nice, with new fixtures, beds and a smaller plasma television. They missed a few things when refurbishing this hotel, though. The shower curtain was old and in desperate need of replacement. There was a smashed spider stuck to the outside of it that looked like it had been there for a while. The air conditioner/heater unit and controller were disgusting and the smoke alarm also needs to be replaced (see photos). I don't get how they could spend so much on updating the rooms and forget the details. We didn't notice a work-out room or a swimming pool while we were there, so those are definitely negatives if those amenities are important to you. My sister and her family stayed at the Golden Nugget, so I went down to visit them at the pool while we were there. We stayed at the GN on our last trip to Vegas, and it was very nice. My in-laws had four free nights at the Plaza and were there for a slot tournament, so we had the room to ourselves. The location of the Four Queens is great since you are smack dab, right in the middle of things on Fremont Street. There is a McDonalds right across the street and a Walgreens within walking distance. We ate at Magnolia's, which is in the hotel, with a buy-one, get-one free coupon from the American Casino Guide (buy on the web or at book stores $14.95-well worth it!). The prime rib was excellent and very reasonable. I would highly recommend this restaurant. We did spend some time in the casino and when we went to the slot club to ask if we had any comps or cash coming back, the slot club attendants were VERY rude. They could really benefit from some basic customer service training. We noticed this on our last visit, and again on this visit. My father-in-law also commented on how rude they were to both he and my mother-in-law.Even though they missed a few things when updating the rooms and the slot club attendants were rude, we will definitely stay at this hotel again since the bed was comfortable and the location is good. I would definitely recommend this hotel to a friend as long as they were not looking for a total resort type of hotel since theres no pool, spa or work-out facility on site. Please feel free to ask any questions regarding our stay.	
Sep 17 2007	Four Queens Was Great!	My Husband and I stayed at Four Queens Sept 13-16th. We have never stayed Downtown before and thought we would give it a try. For a great price we figured how bad could it be? FQ exceeded our expectations!!CHECK IN:The front desk check in was wonderful.... no wait...friendly..and they honored all of our requests. I had asked for a King bed, non smoking, facing the Fremont street side of the hotel.ROOMS:We received a room on the fifth floor (518). We loved facing the Fremont Street Experience it was great! The Four Queens is one of the only hotels downtown that actually has rooms under the &quot;canopy&quot; facing Fremont Street. We could watch the light show right from our room! (people watching was great too!) The even numbered rooms face fremont street. There was some noise from the light show and they play music all day long. It stops at Midnight. No big deal! We kind of enjoyed the music.CASINOThe Casino was good. We saw many other people winning! We didn't!!PARKINGParking was easy. We self parked our car, but they had Valet also. On Saturday night they allowed us VIP PARKING even though the sign said the lot was full.NO POOLThe FQ doesn't have a pool, but honestly...we were so busy, we didn't miss not having it.RESTAURANTSWe ate at Magnolias twice, the food was average, cheap enough, the wait staff left a little to be desired, we had a little language barrier problem with the girl that got the drinks in the restaurant, but the server was average...... Overall it was AVERAGE!! DOWNTOWN AREA The Downtown area has honestly been revitalized. They have so much to offer. There was a Ariel performance, a Motorcycle stunt show, a stage with a variety of performers, plenty of Kiosks selling gifts and snacks. In the evening they brought out rolling bars selling adult beverages. It seemed like a big happy, party, with a fun atmosphere. I will say the FQ is not a Luxury Property, But they don't charge a Luxury price!It fit our needs and I would recommend it to people that are looking for a clean, nice, friendly hotel in downtown......We have stayed at Flamingo, Harrahs, Monte Carlo,Luxor, and Palace Station. Just to give an idea of what we are comparing past stays to.The Four Queens is a solid choice.	
