id was hot. We called the desk to complain about the cold and asked to have someone sent up (at 11pm) to check on the heat. The engineer said the air was on the heater was not, and there was nothing he could do. The staff, except for Anthony the valet, was not friendly at all, and most (including the ones at Magnolia's) seemed inconvenienced by our very presence. The final straw was that on the day we came back from the Hoover dam and all of the guest elevators in the hotel were out of service. We took a service elevator to our floor and were &quot;chewed out&quot; by a cleaning lady for using the elevator that was for service use only. When I explained that my husband, who walks with a cane, has a rod in his leg and is in no shape to walk up and down 19 flights of stairs, she said that wasn't her problem - nice huh?We spent most of our time at Fitzgeralds, the staff there was way friendlier, the food was better, and the slots were looser.I DO NOT recommend this hotel to anyone!	
