Apr 12 2007 	Mediocre experience!!!	I take my 79 year old mother to Vegas once per year. We have stayed on the strip and last year decided to try the DT area. Last year, we stayed at the Golden Nugget, which was fabulous. She likes to go DT now as it is so much smaller and easier for her to get around.This time we decided to try the Four Queens as they have boasted about renovating their rooms. I read good reviews from this site and was not too concerned. Our experience, however, was not the greatest. We were there from April 1-4, 2007.We were put into a room upon which when I went into the bathroom, a huge pubic hair was starring at from the toilet seat. Gross! Unacceptable! There was also long, black hair on the bathroom floor. I did not decide to request another room, however, until the toilet overflowed a few minutes later. YUCK!So, they put us in another room... no problem... until... that toilet overflowed too. It actually overflowed the following day. I suspect that the infostructure of that part of the city is just so old leading to plumbing problems. (At least there were no pubic hairs to be seen in this bathroom) I called about the toilet and they brought up some big and loud as crap machine to soak up the toilet water that made it's way out onto the carpet outside of the bathroom. They left the machine in the room for many, many hours while we were out gambling. When we got back to the room in the early morning the machine was still there roaring away. I unplugged it and put it out into the hallway. Was the toilet water drenched carpet dry? NO. It was better but certainly not dry. I suppose we could have changed rooms again but we were only going to be there for two more nights and my mother didn't want to bother with it. At least we had our house shoes to wear so our feet didn't have to touch that toilet water germ-filled carpet.The next day our A/C went out. I called about it and they sent someone up to correct the problem ASAP. It worked fine after that.I found the front desk staff to be very nice, friendly and helpful. Even though we had room problems, they were diligent about getting those problems corrected.We had fun in the casino but the the servers did not come around too often for drink orders. Had great luck at the ELVIS slot machine located near the players club desk. That machine seemed to be paying out the whole time we were there. I finally got a chance to get on it right before we left for the airport and won $160.00 playing pennies, not even max bet pennies, and still won. Might not sound like a lot but I am by no means a high roller and was happy to win that much. I only put $20.00 in.Had a blast at the BJ tables. Lost the first night but made up for it after that. We also played at Binion's which I love. Aways seem to find decent slot machines there and have a blast playing BJ. So, would I stay at the Four Queens again. NO. I would rather pay a bit more and stay at the Nugget. It is nicer and seems to be kept up WAY better than the Queens. Oh, one more thing, the rooms were indeed renovated and had the big screen TV. But, the choices of bedspreads and curtains were/are appalling. I know this might not matter to many people who read this but the fabric truly looked like it came straight out of the 1970's. Whoever was in charge of choosing those fabrics should be fired and required to go to interior design school. Look at the hotel photos on this site and you will see what I mean.	
