Dec 6 2006 	Closest to street Hotel Rooms	Four Queens room 1501 in the North Tower was close to the elevator in the tower next to the Fremont Street Experience (FSE). You could close your hotel room door, take the elevator and be on the street within about 3 minutes and about 20 steps. This beats the block+ walk through Golden Nugget, Fitzgeralds, and Fremont to get to the street from their rooms. You could not really hear the FSE from the room, but you would on the rooms on the other side lower down. The window had a view of the Nugget and the other Queens tower and parking garage. The room is small about 15x25 total. The window is about 4x15. The bathroom is about 6x 9 and a large closet about 2.5x 5.5. The main room is about 15x15. The furniture is classy mahogany looking including 2x4 table, two table chairs, TV stand with 2 drawers, 2 night stands with 2 drawers, and one king bed. The closet doors are mirrors. The room has central air, alarm clock, hair dryer, standard hotel 3 cup drip coffee maker, $0.75 phone calls, good wireless internet $11.99 per day and room food service. Like most LV hotel rooms the lights were too low of wattage to read. Magnolias Café has excellent food and specials. There is a pizza place and coffee, donuts, ice cream parlor hidden in the corner where Burger King and sushi bar used to be. Maid service was polite, detailed, and excellent. The small 24 remote Philips TV had in room movies. The zip code for the online Yahoo TV schedule is 89101 and Cox Communications (digital) is the cable provider. The room TV stations are:2.KVBC local3.NBC KVBC local5. Fox KVVU local6. CNN 20 Atlanta7. Keno8. CBS KLAS local9. TBSP Atlanta10. PBS KLUX11. CNN- 22 Headline News12. ESPN 3013. ABC KTNV local15. KINC 15 Spanish16. Hotel Dining17. Hotel Gaming23. Movie PreviewsThe North Tower has red key cards and the South Tower has purple. The ice machines in th North Tower are on floors 2, 9, 10, 12, 16, 18, and 19 while the soda machines ($1.50 coin) are on floors 5, 8, 11, 15, and 17.I will stay in the North Tower again since it is so close to the street and other casinos. The room was closer to the front doors and casinos of the Fremont, Binions Horseshoe, and Golden Nugget than the rooms in their own hotels. The down side was the central air could not get the room temperature below 70F easily and the small room and bathroom size. The room check in (on Sundays to get keys to go into the room) could not be before 2 PM and room not guaranteed clean until 4 PM so use the bell hop and wait around with a dirty room or forget the early arrival flight on Sundays. On Monday I saw people checking in starting at 8:30 AM. There was a new airport boarding pass printing machine near the reservation desk for about $1 per minute plus $0.50 per page.	
