Oct 17 2006 	Great for the Price	My husband and I stayed at the Four Queens from October 12 - 16th. While it is not a five star property, it certainly exceeded our expectations, particularly after reading some of the reviews on this site. The staff was attentive and met our expectations. The first night, we smelled a lot of cigarette smoke in the room (despite being on a non-smoking floor). The next day we asked to be moved and were given another room on a different floor without any hassle at all. The rooms (both of them) contained king sized (quite comfortable) beds. They were clean and reasonably well-kept (although somewhat showing their age). We also enjoyed gambling here - they do actually have one $2 blackjack table and you can often get on, if you don't mind waiting for a bit of time. I am new to blackjack and didn't want to spend lots of money learning the ropes. Don't bother with the breakfast (even the $4 special rate if you become a players club member)...the $5.99 buffet (weekdays) at Main Station far exceeds anything you can get at the Four Queens and includes juice and coffee (unlike the $4 breakfast special at the hotel restaurant). All in all, we will stay here again, without hesitation.	
