Oct 10 2005	Ok for 29 bucks...	Stayed here in room 819 on a Tuesday night booked directly through the hotel website for 29 bucks. Check in was less than a minute. Casino is easy to navigate and elevators for both towers easy to find. No security whatsoever checking keys at the elevators. Room was smaller than average motel 6. Bed was similar to sleeping on the floor in comfort level. TV had about 6 or 7 channels. I ended up watching the hotels ammenity channel over and over because the goon and his wife featured were funny to watch. They were SO excited to be at this hotel, it was comical. The worst part of this room was the bathroom. It was the smallest I have ever had. The missing shower tile had been placed on the toilet tank, probably by a guest years previous. The shower drain backed up in less than a minute so you would be mid calf deep in water. The water temp and pressure sucked big time. If you turned the temp up to a decent level, the plumbing behind the wall would vibrate VERY LOUDLY. This would continue to get progressively worse until the knob was backed off enough to give you a nice refreshing ARCTIC BLAST. It would cycle like that throughout the shower. I would not stay again, regardless of the 29 dollar Tuesday. As a side note, the Chicago Brewing Company located inside the casino has excellent pizzas and beer.	
