Sep 5 2005 	A good value friendly staff	On of my two choices when staying downtown on my frequent trips into Las Vegas. I travel on business, but do drop a few bucks in the casinos during my down time and choose 4 Queens or Fitzgeralds for about 80% of my visits. Both hotels have their pros and cons. The 4 Queens has, by far, the better front desk staff...friendly and accomodating (can't say that about most of the staff at the Fitz). Rooms are clean, although a bit outdated, and comfortable with the basic ammenities. The shower generally has poor water pressure and the bathrooms are overall smaller than they should be. Lower floors in the North Tower can be less than peaceful at night during the Freemont St Experience shows so don't plan on a early night's sleep...the noise drops off around midnight...but hey, this is Vegas...who's in their room at midnight (me, unfortunately...when there's business to take care of the next AM). A gift shop near the front desk is open late and 24 hrs on weekends.There is a Subway/Noble Romans Pizza/TCBY location off the lobby, a 24 hour cafe with quality food at reasonable prices, a Chicago Brewing Company with a variety of beers and pizza, and Hugo's Cellar which is a mainstay downtown and known for it's fine dining experience. The casino is small but offers great variety with a wide range of monetary denominations. Dealers are friendly and helpful. The players club is probably the best cash-back program downtown but any comps must go through a host or pit boss.Overall, a good value for the money. For those wishing to stay in the coziness of downtown...4 Queens isn't a bad bet.	
Aug 29 2005	Good stay for a very low price!	We didn't expect much as we had only payed 20 Euro for the night at the 4 Queens. Therefore, we were happy with what we got. The staff at reception was very friendly and helpful to us! The room didn't appear too inviting, it was small with a very small bathroom, kind of old and worn - but clean! For hotel guests the parking garage costs $ 3,- when you show the ticket at reception. We spent one day and night in Downtown which we found enough to see what you have to (Fremont St. Experience, Casinos, restaurants, street musicians).For such a short stay we would come back to the 4 Queens, was a gread deal for the money.	
