May 1 2005	Pleasantly surprised	My husband and I stayed at the Four Queens Tuesday, April 19. We decided we would change our flight if we could find a decent place to stay that was pretty cheap. After reading all the reviews on trip advisor I decided we would give the Four Queens a shot. I called and made the reservation getting a rate cheaper than was on the internet. It was $49 without tax. I requested a king, non smoking in what is supposed to be the nicer tower, ( I can't remember which one it is now). She said they couldn't guarantee that, but they would make the request. I told her the main thing was a non-smoking room. I also advised that our flight would not arrive until 10:00 pm, she made that note as well in case we had flight delays, they would not give our room away. Check in was easy, we got the room we requested (there is only 1 king bed on each floor is what I was told). We took our bags to the room. It was spotless. I was very pleased. We could tell the light show was going on, we could see the top of the canopy, but we hung out in the room for a while, before heading back out to grab a drink and watch the midnight show. It was great to walk out the doors and be on Freemont Street, it was the middle of the week so not very crowded. After the show, we grabbed a bite to eat at McDonalds which was next door and still open. Then went in and crashed, after all it was probably 3am my time. Slept great, the next morning we decided to see if our room at TI was ready, it would be by the time we got there, so we washed our face, brushed our teeth and waited until we got there to take a shower. We didn't use the shower so I don't know about drainage problems. Overall, I would definitely recommend Four Queens and I would stay there again although, I would not spend more than one night, but it was a great experience. We may actually start doing that, taking a late flight and staying downtown for the first night, it was fun!	
