Jan 18 2005	Awesome affordable whirlpool rooms	For someone looking for a reasonably priced hotel, try the 4 Queens in the downtown. We actually started in a standard room which was okay, but the second day, we upgraded to a deluxe whirlpool room, which overlooked the Fremont Street experience and had a city and mountain view. This room made the whole trip!!! Didn't think we would use the whirlpool much, but after a day of walking (everyday), it was a great way to relax before doing the night shows, gambling, and just people watching. The downtown casinos really all look alike, but the table game minimums are lower than on the strip and it is a much shorter walk to more casinos &amp; resturants.	
