Sep 22 2004	Good time for cheap!	I was at the Four Queens for 5 nights during Bikefest 2004. The room was small but had all the necessary things.... TV, table and chairs, and a clean bed and bathroom. The furniture was fairly new and the room was bright and comfortable. The view was blocked by the Fremont Street canopy so basically there was no view, and the noise from the constant music and events happening on Fremont Street might be annoying to some, but I like the sounds of Vegas and it wasn't extemely loud so that didn't bother me. The casino itself is pretty small but nice. The restaurants were also very good. They include a cigar/microbrew lounge that I spent several nights in; a coffee shop that serves good food but the service could have been better, and a dressy restaurant called Hugo's that is more pricey, but still way below comparable restaurants on the south end of the strip, and the service and food were outstanding. All in all, I really enjoyed this hotel/casino. And at $39 a night it's a real bargain.	
