Mar 30 2004	We like the Four Queens but its not the Ritz.	Not the ritz, but a good value. Our rooms were complimentary but even at normal price they are very reasonable. We have stayed at the Four Queens 3 times now, and like the location downtown. The casino has some good action; roulette and good nickle slots. The $7.99 prime rib in Magnolias is very good, and the food is served hot. During our last stay, the a/c wasn't working in our room, but I am sure we could have moved to another room, but chose not to. At the end of the stay, I wish we had, as it was warm at night. The rooms are clean with small bathroom but super water pressure made great showers. During our stay, only two elevators out of four were working properly, so I rode up, just to get a space in the elevator going down. This is unusual as all four were working for our other stays. Valet parking is free for hotel guests. You can watch Keno in the room for a change of pace; the live Keno is downstairs. Acrsoss the street is the Golden Nugget which has loose dollar slots. 1 block down to the Lady Luck, which can also be lucky. Where ever you play, be sure to get a players card to get comps. I'll give Four Queens 2 1/2 stars, but after all, in Vegas, how much time do you want spend in the room?	
