Sep 28 2003	Four Queens better than expected	The room was clean and comfortable and we really enjoyed the Fremont Street Experience. We got a special deal on the room thru Expedia and we were not disappointed.	
Aug 8 2003	Four Queens was a Lady!	We found the staff at the Four Queens to be most graceful and willing to help with any request. Our room was nothing special, but it was clean and comfortable. The housekeeping person apparently did not know the difference in shampoo and body lotion, after three days, we had three bottles of lotion, but no shampoo (fortunately, we had some of our own). We have always enjoyed the casino in the Four Queens, but this trip we did not spend much time there because the temperature (according to a display on the wall) was between 76 and 77 degrees F. This may be okay for many, but we found it uncomfortably warm. Will we go there again? Absolutely!!	
Jul 23 2003	Affordable Luxury	The Four Queens has nothing to offer other than its casino as far as ameneties go - not even a pool. However! walking through the hotel gives you a sense of pride, as if your staying at a 4 or 5 star hotel due to the shiny mirrors and bright lights that give the hotel a glitzy and glamorous feel. Just step outside the hotel and your right in the heart of the Freemont Experience where every night from 8-12 they have exciting and awesome laser light shows and there is plenty to do right on Fremont St. without having to drive to the strip (10 minutes by car) the room was nice and the bathroom included complimentary travel sized shampoo/conditioner. Not a big deal but again, considering the room rates, your lucky to get any. The hotel has free enclosed parking which should keep your car cool should you have one. Overall, it wasn't the greatest place to stay, but it provided what really matter most, a clean room and comfortable room at a fraction of what you would pay for anything comparable.	
Jul 15 2003	Fabulous Four Queens	I submitted this to Diane Chapman of the Four QueensI would like to start by saying Thank You. Thank you for a wonderful five day stay at the Four Queens! My husband and I miss the &quot;old&quot; Vegas and you provide the nostalgic atmosphere missing from all of the new &quot;sterile&quot; resorts and casinos.Your staff was cheerful, helpful and always pleasant; we intend to suggest your hotel to ALL of our associates. Our stay was made even more enjoyable by the generosity of your gaming facility! The refrigerator in our room was not cooling properly, we called and waited approx. 10 minutes, unbelievable, the response time was record breaking, your Engineer replaced the unit, all with a smile! We couldn't help but remark at how knowledgeable and informative all of your staff was, including your Security Department.Our room was clean and spacious; we enjoyed your instantaneous room service, on demand movies and the convenience of your taxi service. One thing absolutely stood out during our stay and this may sound strange, considering the climate during our visit BUT please commend your superb Chef on the delectable MINESTRONE soup, what a delightful &quot;elixir&quot;, such an unexpected taste treat.We have read reviews on your hotel rooms and were surprised by some suggesting that you try and stay as far from the Fremont St. experience as possible, because of the noise. We were on the ninth floor overlooking the Fremont and thoroughly enjoyed the nightly light show, honestly if you visit Las Vegas for a quiet nights sleep, something is wrong with you. We had the opportunity to enjoy a few fireworks on Thursday night; we could see them through our window, coming from the direction of the Stratosphere.We regretted having to leave on Monday morning BUT even upon our departure everyone we encountered was as gracious as when we checked in. The gentleman that retrieved our bags from our room was kind enough to unload our bags into our car in the Valet area and your Valet Attendant was also very pleasant. Please pass this along to your staff and their Superiors; everyone enjoys a well-deserved pat on the back, sincere praise, thanks, or a compliment. Well, we have decided that five days is just not enough to really enjoy Vegas, so we will just have to come back. Thank you, again Diane.	
